section.section:
The purpose of the program is to provide for victims of domestic violence and their children, in each region of this State:
temporary shelter or help in obtaining shelter;
counseling;
information;
referral; and
rehabilitation.

text.section:
Any program established under this section shall be subject to the following conditions:
the program shall provide victims of domestic violence and their children with a temporary home and necessary counseling;
the Governor's Office of Crime Control and Prevention shall:
supervise the program;
set standards of care and admission policies;
monitor the operation of the program and annually evaluate the effectiveness of the program;
adopt rules and regulations that set fees for services at and govern the operation of each program; and
regularly consult, collaborate with, and consider the recommendations of the federally recognized State domestic violence coalition regarding domestic violence programs and policies, practices, and procedures that impact victims of domestic violence and their children;
the program shall accept from the police or any other referral source in the community any victim of domestic violence and the child of any victim of domestic violence; and
housing may not be provided under this subtitle to an applicant for housing who is not a resident of this State at the time the application for housing is made.
